        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(slack): default member-info userId to inbound sender",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Let Slack `member-info` omit `userId` in a current Slack conversation and default to the trusted inbound sender.\n- Require the source provider and canonical Slack account to match the target; cross-channel and cross-account calls still require an explicit `userId`.\n- Carry trusted requester account identity with requester sender identity through local and gateway-owned message action dispatch.\n\nAn explicit `userId` always wins.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe Slack tool schema already makes `userId` optional, but dispatch required it unconditionally. Defaulting only from `requesterSenderId` was not sufficient: sender IDs are provider- and workspace-scoped, so provider and account identity must travel together.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/slack/src/message-action-dispatch.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/send.test.ts src/agents/tools/message-tool.test.ts` — 4 shards, 275 tests passed\n- Azure Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` — passed; run `run_b53ae65825ba`, lease `cbx_820e5280e6d5`\n- Azure Crabbox `pnpm build` — passed; run `run_1c11f81d85ff`, same lease (stopped)\n- Fresh branch autoreview — no actionable findings; correctness confidence 0.94\n- `git diff --check` and focused formatting — passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Slack `member-info` no longer fails with `userId required` when called from a same-account Slack turn without an explicit user id.\n- Real environment tested: OpenClaw Slack action dispatch, message-tool, local plugin-dispatch, and Gateway action seams; Linux type/lint/guard/build proof on Azure Crabbox.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/slack/src/message-action-dispatch.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/send.test.ts src/agents/tools/message-tool.test.ts`\n- Evidence after fix: 275 targeted tests passed; remote changed gate and full build passed.\n- Observed result after fix: same-provider, same-canonical-account calls use the trusted inbound Slack sender; configured default and case-normalized account ids work; missing, cross-provider, and cross-account context rejects unless `userId` is explicit.\n- What was not tested: a live Slack workspace call. The API invocation itself is unchanged; focused proof covers the new identity-selection and propagation behavior.\n\n## Compatibility and risk\n\n- Additive optional `requesterAccountId` field in the channel action context and Gateway `message.action` request.\n- No config, migration, permission, token, or dependency changes.\n- The account check prevents a Slack workspace-local user id from being reused with another account token.\n",
        "branch": "fix/slack-member-info-default-sender",
